subSubSection.paragraph:
Medium-sized (5.4 mm), black-bronze, matt with silky lustre (
Fig. 1
); clypeus and anterior portion of frons with weak, violet lustre; ventral surface lustrous, black-violet; entire dorsal surface asetose, ventral surface with rather long, sparse, recumbent white pubescence, metepisterna covered with cream-white tomentum.

The holotype was originally pinned, so the right elytron and corresponding portion of the abdomen are somewhat damaged (see 
Fig. 1
).
